}</ref>\n\n'''2013'''\n\nChina Entrepreneurs Magazine-China's Top Women Business Leaders\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|3}} jiao graduation\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://www.xiaojukeji.com/news/newslisten Corporate Website of Didi Chuxing]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Liu, Qing}}\n[[Category:Businesspeople from Beijing]]\n[[Category:1978 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Peking University alumni]]\n[[Category:Harvard University alumni]]\n[[Category:Chinese women business executives]]\n[[Category:Chinese chief operating officers]]\n[[Category:Goldman Sachs people]]\n[[Category:DiDi people]]\n", "text_old": "{{Chinese name|[[Liu (\u67f3)|Li\u01d4 (\u67f3)]]}}\n\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Jean Liu\n| image         = Jean Liu DiDi (3).jpg\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = Jean Liu (2017 photo)\n| birth_name    = Liu Qing <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{birth year and age|1978}}\n| birth_place   = Beijing, China\n| death_date    = <!-- {{Death date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|YYYY|MM|DD}} (death date then birth date)  -->\n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = Chinese\n| other_names   = \n| occupation    = Business Executive\n| years_active  = \n| known_for     = President of Didi Chuxing\n| notable_works = \n| alma_mater = [[Peking University]] (B.S., Computer Science, 2000)<br>[[Harvard University]] (M.S., Computer Science, 2002)<ref name=\"HARVARDALUMCOUNCIL\">[https://gsas.harvard.edu/person/jean-liu \"Profile: Jean Liu\"], Harvard University Graduate School of Arts and Sciences, Alumni Council</ref>\n| relatives = [[Lenovo]] founder [[Liu Chuanzhi]] (father)\n}}\n'''Liu Qing''' ({{zh|c=|s=\u67f3\u9752|t=\u67f3\u9752|p=Li\u01d4 Q\u012bng}}, born 1978 in [[Beijing]]) or '''Jean Liu''', is a Chinese business executive. Liu is the President of [[Didi Chuxing]] (\"DiDi\", formerly known as Didi Kuaidi), China's largest mobile transportation platform.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/business/tech/2016-06/13/content_25690974.htm|title=Didi Chuxing receives $600m investment from China Life Insurance  - Business - Chinadaily.com.cn|last=\u5b8b\u9759\u4e3d|website=www.chinadaily.com.cn|access-date=2016-09-08}}</ref> She worked at [[Goldman Sachs]] Asia for 12 years, becoming a managing director in 2012, before switching to Didi Dache serving as its chief operating officer in July 2014.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/ywang/2014/11/05/tencent-backed-didi-dache-pursues-buses-government-cars-after-daughter-of-lenovos-liu-chuanzhi-joined/#72af7e917721|title=Tencent-Backed Didi Dache Pursues Buses, Government Cars After Daughter of Lenovo's Liu Chuanzhi Joined|newspaper=Forbes}}</ref>\n\nAfter joining Didi Dache, she led the strategic merger between Didi Dache and its main competitor Kuaidi Dache which then created a new car hailing company named Didi Kuaidi (later rebranded as Didi Chuxing) in 2015.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.ft.com/content/4b0a0c56-5afb-11e6-9f70-badea1b336d4|title=Jean Liu: Splashing the cash|last=Clover|first=Charles|last2=Hook|first2=Leslie|newspaper=Financial Times|issn=0307-1766|access-date=2016-09-08}}</ref> \n\n==Early life and education==\nLiu was born in 1978 in Beijing, China. She is the daughter of Chinese businessman and [[Lenovo]] founder [[Liu Chuanzhi]], and the granddaughter of Liu Gushu, a senior executive banker at the [[Bank of China]]. She received a bachelor's degree in Computer Science at [[Peking University]], and a master's degree in Computer Science at [[Harvard University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Jean Liu: She Was Asked to Sing C\u00e9line Dion in a Job Interview, Now She\u2019s Uber\u2019s Greatest Threat in China|url=http://nextshark.com/jean-liu-didi-dache/|website=NextShark}}</ref> She received an honorary Doctor of Commercial Science from New York University. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.nyu.edu/content/nyu/en/about/news-publications/news/2018/april/canadian-prime-minister-justin-trudeau-to-speak-at-nyus-186th-co|title=Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau to Speak at NYU\u2019s 186th Commencement|last=Communications|first=NYU Web|language=en|access-date=2018-08-06}}</ref>\n\n== Personal life ==\nLiu currently lives in Beijing with her family. In October 2015, Liu announced internally that she was being treated for breast cancer at the age of 37.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.scmp.com/news/china/society/article/1863839/boss-didi-kuaidi-mainland-china-gets-treated-breast-cancer|title=Boss of Didi Kuaidi in mainland China gets treated for breast cancer|access-date=2016-09-08}}</ref> In early December 2015, she posted on her Weibo that she would return to work by the end of December after a two-month treatment.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.allchinatech.com/president-of-didi-kuaidi-liu-qing-being-expected-to-return-to-work-by-the-end-of-month/|title=Didi Kuaidi's president Jean Liu plans to return to work by the end of December - AllChinaTech|last=Li|first=Danielle|date=2015-12-08|language=en-US|access-date=2016-09-08|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160917022020/http://www.allchinatech.com/president-of-didi-kuaidi-liu-qing-being-expected-to-return-to-work-by-the-end-of-month/|archivedate=2016-09-17}}</ref> According to DiDi, she is now fine and \"has been in all-in mode for quite some time\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/4b0a0c56-5afb-11e6-9f70-badea1b336d4,Authorised=false.html?siteedition=intl&_i_location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcms%2Fs%2F0%2F4b0a0c56-5afb-11e6-9f70-badea1b336d4.html%3Fsiteedition%3Dintl&_i_referer=&classification=conditional_standard&iab=barrier-app|title=Jean Liu: Splashing the cash|last=Clover|first=Charles|last2=Hook|first2=Leslie|newspaper=Financial Times|issn=0307-1766|access-date=2016-09-08}}</ref>\n\nAfter being named one of the \"50 Most Powerful Moms of 2016\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.workingmother.com/50-most-powerful-moms-2016#page-24|title=Introducing the 50 Most Powerful Moms of 2016|access-date=2016-09-08}}</ref> by ''Working Mother'', Liu spoke about how she balanced working for DiDi with her relationship with her three kids.\n\n== Awards and honors ==\n'''2018'''\n\nChina Entrepreneurs Magazine-China's Top 10 Business Women in 10 years<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/9fi5bYVGEv-_2K0Y-b3AnQ|title=\u4e2d\u56fd\u6700\u5177\u5f71\u54cd\u529b\u5546\u754c\u5973\u6027-10\u5e74\u202210\u4eba}}</ref>\n\nForbes-2018 Forbes China Top 100 Businesswomen<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/russellflannery/2018/03/03/2018-forbes-china-top-100-businesswomen-list-full-list/#67327dc11d2c|title=2018 Forbes China Top 100 Businesswomen List (Full List)|last=Flannery|first=Russell|work=Forbes|access-date=2018-08-06|language=en}}</ref>\n\n'''2017'''\n\nTIME-The 100 Most Influential People<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://time.com/collection/2017-time-100/4742753/jean-liu/|title=Jean Liu: The World\u2019s 100 Most Influential People|website=Time|language=en-us|access-date=2018-08-06}}</ref>\n\nFortune-Most Powerful Women International<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://fortune.com/most-powerful-women-international/jean-liu-25/|title=Jean Liu|date=2017-09-25|work=Fortune|access-date=2018-08-06|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\nRecode-Recode 100<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.recode.net/2017/12/6/16680996/jean-liu-did-chuxing-china-transportation-company-recode-100|title=Jean Liu is leading one of the world\u2019s most powerful transportation companies|work=Recode|access-date=2018-08-06}}</ref>\n\nAsia society-Asia Game Changer<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://asiasociety.org/asia-game-changers/jean-liu|title=Jean Liu - 2017 Asia Game Changers|work=Asia Society|access-date=2018-08-06|language=en}}</ref>\n\nForbes-The World's Most Powerful Women In Tech 2017<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carolinehoward/2017/11/01/the-worlds-most-powerful-women-in-tech-2017-still-a-minority-their-clout-is-